{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "glow", "icon": "VOP/glow", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Glow"], "extent": [59, 68]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates a hot glow effect to be used in the Fog context, and\noutputs color and alpha."], "extent": [68, 164]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates a hot glow effect to be used in the Fog context,\nand outputs color and alpha."], "extent": [164, 267]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Unlike Halo, which produces a generic, white-light glow, this operator\nis meant for glows around lights, flames, and other hot point sources."], "extent": [267, 410]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Core parameters control the white hotspot at the very center of the\nglow. For a softer, less hot glow, set the Core Brightness (corebright)\nvalue to 0."], "extent": [410, 567]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The glow color is multiplied by the Opacity (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Of"]}, ") before being mixed with\nthe Surface Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, "), so you do not have to take opacity into account\nyourself."], "extent": [567, 727]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Surface Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, "), Position of Eye (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Eye"]}, "), Surface Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, ")\nSurface Opacity (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Of"]}, "), and Surface Alpha (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Af"]}, ") inputs are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. If you need\nto access the global variables directly, they are available from the\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [727, 1067]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For a simple glow, connect the color output (", {"type": "code", "text": ["color"]}, ") and the alpha output\n(", {"type": "code", "text": ["alpha"]}, ") to the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, " and respectively ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Af"]}, " inputs of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, "\noperator."], "extent": [1067, 1248]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1248, 1257], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}], "extent": [1257, 1281]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/halo", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/halo"}], "extent": [1281, 1303]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}], "extent": [1303, 1328]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Glow"], "summary": ["Simulates a hot glow effect to be used in the Fog context, and\noutputs color and alpha."]}